item.title: New TT items
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

abatssk8ter:

My Buddy got a bandos robe bottem from a TT yesterday, Should he keep till it rises or sell? will it even rise?

It won’t rise until people sell it. I am sure many people are buying it for maximum price right now, in which it will rise if people sell it.

The economy isn’t going to get fucked. The new items do not pump any great bonuses or gold into the game. The only thing that is going to change is the price of the old treasure trail items and the new ones. I am sure once everyone settles down, no one will care about these as much as they do now. Most likely items such as the 3rd age druidic robe will be turned into junk for trading.

As far as I know, these clues are long and difficult. They are only dropped by higher-leveled monsters (such as metal dragons, Bork, Corporeal Beast, etc.). I have seen a few clan members get them and they said they are as long as hell.

It’s a new update. Obviously the items are going to rise in price, people are going to mass-kill high leveled monsters aiming to get one, and everyone is going to flash2:panic when they get a good reward. Let the prices and people settle down, it’s only been a day.
